<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">General distribution: Northwest Europe</emphasis>
: Denmark, Estonia, Finland, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Norway, Sweden; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Southern Europe</emphasis>
: Bulgaria, Croatia, France, Greece, Italy (including Sicily), Montenegro, North Macedonia, Romania, Slovenia, Serbia, Spain; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Central Europe</emphasis>
: Austria, Belgium, Czech Republic, Germany, Hungary, Netherlands, Poland, Slovakia, Switzerland; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">British Isles</emphasis>
: United Kingdom; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Eastern Europe</emphasis>
: Moldavia, Russia, Ukraine; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Middle East</emphasis>
: Iran, Palestine, Turkey; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Transcaucasia</emphasis>
: Azerbaijan, Georgia, Russia (Dagestan); 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Central Asia</emphasis>
: Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Russia (Bashkiria, Chuvashia), Tajikistan; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Siberia</emphasis>
: Russia (Southern Siberia); 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Eastern Asia</emphasis>
: China (Heilongjiang, Sichuan), Korea, Russia (Primorsky Krai, Sakhalin) (summarised by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nast, Janusz" journalOrPublisher="Polish Scientific Publishers, Warszawa" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" refId="B5743322" refString="Nast, Janusz, 1972. Palaearctic Auchenorrhyncha (Homoptera). An annotated check list. Polish Scientific Publishers, Warszawa" title="Palaearctic Auchenorrhyncha (Homoptera). An annotated check list" year="1972">Nast 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kudryasheva, J. V." journalOrPublisher="Nauka, Moskva" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" refId="B5743179" refString="Kudryasheva, J. V., 1979. Lichinki pevchikh tsikad (Homoptera, Cicadidae) fauny SSSR. Nauka, Moskva" title="Lichinki pevchikh tsikad (Homoptera, Cicadidae) fauny SSSR" year="1979">Kudryasheva 1979</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Duffels, J P" journalOrPublisher="Dr W Junk Publisher, Dordrecht, Boston, Lancaster" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" refId="B5742783" refString="Duffels, J P, van der Laan, P A, 1985. Catalogue of the Cicadoidea (Homoptera, Auchenorhyncha) 1956-1980. Dr W Junk Publisher, Dordrecht, Boston, Lancaster" title="Catalogue of the Cicadoidea (Homoptera, Auchenorhyncha) 1956 - 1980" year="1985">Duffels and van der Laan 1985</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, Allen F" journalOrPublisher="Academic Press / Elsevier, London, UK" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" refId="B5743532" refString="Sanborn, Allen F, 2014. Catalogue of the Cicadoidea. Academic Press/Elsevier, London, UK" title="Catalogue of the Cicadoidea" year="2014">Sanborn 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Distribution in Bulgaria</emphasis>
: In addition to a single literature citation by 
<bibRefCitation author="Yoakimov, D" journalOrPublisher="Sbornik za narodni umotvoreniya, nauka i knizhnina [Collection of folklore, science and literature]" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="1 - 34" refId="B5743855" refString="Yoakimov, D, 1909. Po faunata na Hemiptera v Blgariya [On the fauna of Hemiptera of Bulgaria]. Sbornik za narodni umotvoreniya, nauka i knizhnina [Collection of folklore, science and literature] 25 (7): 1 - 34" title="Po faunata na Hemiptera v Blgariya [On the fauna of Hemiptera of Bulgaria]" volume="25" year="1909">Yoakimov (1909)</bibRefCitation>
, the specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="s. lat. (Scopoli" authorityYear="1772" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadetta montana" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Cicadetta montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s. lat. were found in the BFUS, SOFM and ZISB collections (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 32" captionStartId="F5781319" captionText="Figure 32. Map with localities of Cicadetta montana s. lat. in Bulgaria. Black - literature data, blue - data from collections." figureDoi=".figure32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/407002" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">32</figureCitation>
). With the exception of some specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schedl" authorityYear="1999" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadetta macedonica" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macedonica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Cicadetta macedonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we could not determine the majority at the specific level only on the basis of morphological characteristics. Additionally, the altitudinal distribution (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 33" captionStartId="F5781323" captionText="Figure 33. Altitudinal distribution of Cicadetta montana s. lat. The percentage of the recorded localities is displayed in 200 - metre altitude zones." figureDoi=".figure33" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443789" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">33</figureCitation>
) of this material with three peaks between sea level and 200 m a.s.l., 400 and 600 m a.s.l. and 1000 and 1200 m a.s.l., shows that within the material in the collections, there is most probably more than one species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Materials</emphasis>
: Suppl. material 7
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">
Singing activity is a very important mechanism used by male cicadas to attract females and is therefore species-specific (e.g. Gogala &amp; Trilar 2004). Recent bioacoustic studies have shown that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="s. lat. (Scopoli" authorityYear="1772" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadetta montana" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Cicadetta montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Scopoli 1772), once thought to be a single widespread Palearctic cicada species, is, in fact, a complex of morphologically-similar sister species that are best characterised by their song patterns. With the help of bioacoustic methods, we find four species from this complex in Bulgaria: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="s. lat. (Scopoli" authorityYear="1772" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadetta montana" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Cicadetta montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s. str. (Scopoli, 1772), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="s. lat. Fieber" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadetta brevipennis" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipennis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Cicadetta brevipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fieber, 1876, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sueur and Puissant" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadetta cantilatrix" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cantilatrix">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Cicadetta cantilatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Sueur and Puissant, 2007 and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schedl" authorityYear="1999" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadetta macedonica" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macedonica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Cicadetta macedonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Schedl, 1999.
</paragraph>
